I meant " responsibility " to vote for our next governor . Oh sure , you say . " I 'll vote . That race is n't until November . " That reply could n't be more wrong ! The governor 's race is going to be decided May 15 with our primary ballots . Gov. Kate Brown is going for another term . According to my voter 's pamphlet , she 's up against a few strong Republican candidates and no strong Democrats or Independents . If you love Kate , you can ignore her primary . But if you want to see Oregon cooperate with federal law and return to the Constitution and restore the American brand of freedom and justice for all under God the way our Constitution was designed , then you must vote as a Republican to vote for one of Kate 's serious contenders . It does n't matter how you feel about Trump or the establishment swamp in D.C. The only way to return to traditional values to govern this state this election cycle is to pick a Republican who can beat Kate . Donna Raagas , Beaverton
